Smoked Honey Teriyaki Ribs are a must right now! 🍖 🍯 🔥
.
Have not made some smoked pork ribs in a while, so I decided to make something unique with these Smoked Honey Teriyaki Ribs. While they might not be the traditional flavor profile for ribs, they hold their own in deliciousness. Glazed with a sweet but savory Honey Teriyaki sauce for an amazing crust. Juicy pork ribs smoked perfectly thanks to the offset smoker. Find the whole recipe on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/smoked-honey-teriyaki-ribs/ 🍻 👍
.
.
.
#overthefirecooking

node.text:
Chimichurri Marinated Tri-Tip with Fries 🥩 🌿 🍟 🔥
.
Throwback to when I cooked some Chimichurri Tri-Tip in the fire pit with some fries and extra chimichurri on the side. This has become a go-to recipe for me when cooking for friends, and I might be doing it this weekend at a big event! Marinated this fat-cap-on tri-tip over night in homemade chimichurri. Grilled over the fire pit for about 1.5 hours to slowly cook it till it hit about 130F. I flipped it often so I could get an even crust! Cooked up some fries in my cast iron in peanut oil then seasoned them with salt garlic pepper from @spiceology. Slice it up on my cutting board , topped the fries with the steak and topped the steak with more chimichurri. This is a Wolfpack favorite for sure! 👍 🔥
.
.
.
Ingredients
Steak: 1 fat cap on tri-tip.
Chimichurri Marinade: 1/4 cup of chopped parsley, 3 tbsp of red wine vinegar, 5-6 chopped garlic cloves, 1 tsp of salt, 1 tsp of pepper, 1 tsp of red chili flakes and 3 tbsp of olive oil.
Fries: 2 fry cut russet potatoes, 2 cups of peanut oil and 1 tbsp of Salt Garlic Pepper from @spiceology.
.
.
.
#overthefirecooking

Smoked Peruvian Chicken is on the menu today! 🍗 🌿 🔥
.
Using some apple chips, I smoked this bad boy till it was juicy & tender. All in all, the seasonings & herbs combined with the apple wood smoke really made it worth all the work! 🍻
.
.
Instructions:
First, I spatchcocked the chicken by taking the backbone out. In a bowl, I mixed chopped garlic, aji amarillo, paprika, black pepper, oregano, cumin, lime juice, honey, salt & olive oil until it was a paste. I lathered that onto the chicken and let it marinate in the fridge for 2 hours. Set my smoker for 275F, then placed some @westernbbqwood apple wood chips on top of the charcoal to start smoking. Let the chicken smoke indirectly for 1-1.5 hours or until it hits 165 internal. While the chicken is cooking, I mixed mayonnaise, chopped garlic, chopped cilantro and lime juice to make a Cilantro Lime Mayo for dipping. Pulled the chicken off and let rest for 5 minutes. Then, I devoured it!
.
.
.

Pineapple Sriracha Shrimp Bowls that taste even better than they look! 🦐🍍🔥
.
Pineapple Sriracha Shrimp Bowls for the perfect sweet, spicy tang we all know and love. My good friends at @oklahomajoes just dropped a new grill, the Blackjack Kettle Charcoal Grill, which gave me the perfect opportunity to throw down on some shrimp bowls. I made a quick pineapple marinade for these shrimp and completed the meal with sriracha mayo and cilantro lime rice. Throw it all in a pineapple bowl for that extra wow factor. Find the whole recipe on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/pineapple-sriracha-shrimp-bowls/
.

node.text:
Scored & Grilled Boneless Beef Short Ribs over the fire today! 🥩 🔪 🌿 🔥
.
A few weeks back, one of my friends described to me the process of scoring meat like a hassleback potato. For more tough cuts like beef short ribs, it helps the marinade tenderize the meat more and give a larger surface area to get a nice crust. I scored these boneless beef short ribs and let them marinate overnight in a soy sauce, sriracha, rice wine vinegar, sesame seed oil and Korean BBQ seasoning mixture. Grilled them for 4-5 minutes per side and glazed with some fish sauce for an extra tang right at the end. I pulled them off around 130F. They were super tender and delicious! Highly recommend this technique! Find more recipes like this on my blog: www.overthefirecooking.com!🍻 👍
.
.
.
Steaks:
- 5-6 Boneless Beef Short Rib filets
- Fish Sauce, for glaze 
- Scallions, for garnish 
- Sesame Seeds, for garnish
.
Marinade:
- 2 tbsp of Korean BBQ Seasoning
- 1/2 cup of Soy Sauce 
- 1/4 cup of Rice Vinegar
- 2 Limes, juiced
- 2 tsp of Sesame Seed Oil
.
Instructions:
1. Take your beef ribs and score them across about 1/4 inch deep on both sides.
3. In a food safe bowl, add your beef and marinade. Mix and set in fridge for 4 hours or ideally overnight.
4. Preheat your grill to medium-high temperature (around 375F).
5. Add steaks to grill and cook for about 4-5 minutes per side or until they are 130F internal. Towards the end, glaze with fish sauce for a nice finishing crust.
6. Pull steak off once done and rest for 7-8 minutes. Top with scallions, sesame seeds and enjoy!
.
.
.
#overthefirecooking

Honey Garlic Sriracha Fried Wings are in it to wing it 🍗 🍯 🌶 🔥
.
I have been craving some grilled and fried chicken wings for the past couple of days. Don’t get me wrong, I love the holiday roasts. But sometimes, you cannot beat the classics like this Honey Garlic Sriracha Fried Wings recipe. Loaded up with the new @spiceology and @huyfongfoods sriracha seasoning for the win (or wing). Find the recipe on my blog or linked in my bio: https://overthefirecooking.com/honey-garlic-sriracha-fried-wings/ 🍻 👍

Cilantro Lime Butter Scallops for the win! 🌿 🔥
.
That’s right, today we’re talking about these Cilantro Lime Butter Scallops! Making a frequent appearance on high end restaurant menus, scallops are like a white cylinder canvas just waiting to be turned into something delicious. They’re from the saltwater clam family, and even have electric blue eyes before they reach your plate! Don’t believe me? (PSA: Yes, I forgot to take off the side muscle… sorry) Just ask google…Find the whole recipe on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/cilantro-lime-butter-scallops/ 🍻👍

node.text:
Lemon Chili Bacon Wrapped Chicken Skewers over the fire 🍗 🥓 🍋 🌶 🔥
.
For a while now, I have been wanting to make this recipe. After seeing some South American cooks use bacon wrapped chicken on skewers, I knew that it was on the to do list sooner than later. Seasoned these guys with my own version of Peri Peri Sauce. This is a spicy citrus sauce that goes really well on chicken. It also cuts through the fat of the bacon nicely to make a savory, spicy and citrusy flavor. Grilled over a medium to medium-low fire to prevent flare ups, this Lemon Chili Bacon Wrapped Chicken Skewers were a bomb recipe for the backyard. Cheers! 🍻 👍
.
.
.
Ingredients:
.
Chicken Skewers:
- 2 lbs of Chicken Breast, cubed
- 18-20 Bacon Slices, cut in half
- Lemon juice, garnish
- Cilantro, garnish
.
Lemon Chili Sauce
- 2 Whole Habaneros
- 4-5 Garlic Cloves
- 1/8 cup of Cilantro
- 2 tbsp of White Vinegar
- 1 tbsp of Chipotle Powder
- 1 tbsp Dried Oregano
- 1 Lemon, juiced
- Oil, as needed
.
Steps:
- In a blender, mix the Lemon Chili sauce until smooth. Reverse 1/8 cup of sauce, then mix the rest over the chicken. Marinate for at least 2 hours or ideally overnight.
- Preheat grill for 3 zone cooking at medium heat (around 300F). - Wrap the chicken in bacon them securely skewer. Fill skewer as best as possible.
- Place skewers on grill. Rotate as needed to prevent flare ups. Cook until the chicken reaches 165F internal.
- Once chicken is close to done, preheat your reserve marinade and baste over the top of the chicken. Once chicken is done, pull and let rest for 2-3 minutes.
- Top chicken with chopped cilantro and lemon juice. Slice and enjoy!
.
.
.

Skewers from @superskewers
.
.

node.text:
Smoked Cheesy Bacon Lobster Tails for an epic backyard feast 🦞 🧀 💨🔥
.
If you don’t think cheese and seafood go together, then you have obviously never had Lobster Mac and Cheese! These Smoked Cheesy Lobster Tails are just that (save the carbs) for an epic feast. Find the cheese recipe below. Also, find more recipes like this on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/ 🍻 👍
.
.
Ingredients:
- 2 tbsp of Butter
- 5 garlic Cloves, chopped
- 2 tbsp of cooked Bacon Bits
- 1/4 cup of Heavy Cream
- 1/4 cup of Jack Cheese
- 1 tbsp of Chives
.
Directions:
1. Melt butter in medium high heat skillet. Add garlic to brown (2 mins).
2. Add bacon and let cook for 2 more minutes.
3. Finally, lower your temperature to low and add cream, cheese and chives. Mix thoroughly and let simmer over fire till thickened (about 8-10 mins). Stir frequently.
4. Pull off, let rest for 2-3 minutes and enjoy
.
.
.

node.text:
Cheesy Steak Pinwheels are epically delicious! 🥩 🧀 🔥
.
As a child, I was always told not to play with my food. Little did they know that I would do that as an adult all the time! These Cheesy Steak Pinwheels are no exception to that rule. Filleted open center cut beef tenderloin stuffed with mustard, cheese and prosciutto. We will then roll these guys up, skewer and slice into individual steaks to be grilled on the @oklahomajoes Blackjack Kettle Grill. Topped with Spicy Gremolata, this is some food worth playing with! Find the whole recipe on my blog: https://overthefirecooking.com/cheesy-steak-pinwheels/  🍻 👍
.

Fried Pancetta Empanadas are my new favorite thing! 🥓 🧀 🔥
.
Throwback ASMR video of these Fried Pancetta Empanadas. Seared up some pancetta and sautéed that with jalapeños, garlic and onion. Added that to a bowl with cream cheese, more cheese and scallions to mix together for the empanadas. *Note* I still have much to learn on the “sealing” method for the empanadas, but I could not resist trying it. Fried these guys up, paired with a Citrus Herb Chimichurri and we are ready to go! Find the recipe on my blog or linked in my bio: https://overthefirecooking.com/fried-pancetta-empanadas/ 🍻 👍
.

Lemon Chili Rye Rotisserie Chicken giving our whole chicken a bit of spice with some tang. Following the release of my new Spirit-Infused Blends with @spiceology, here’s a recipe with the Lemon Chili Rye rub. While it’s fantastic on chicken, seafood, pork and veggies; it can also double as the rim seasoning for a cocktail or sprinkled within for some extra flare. node.text:
What do bourbon, rye, mezcal and sake have in common? 🥩 🍤 🥃 🍸🔥
.
They make food taste amazing cooked over fire! I am so stoked to announce my brand new Spirit Seasoning line with @spiceology. With four brand new seasonings, you will get to try some crazy new flavors that just might become staple pieces on your grill. To celebrate, I paired with my good friend Drew Nix to grill a feast over the fire along with four different cocktails inspired by the seasonings themselves. Find out about each seasoning below, and make sure to snag them all clicking the link in my bio or on @spiceology’s website: https://spiceology.com/derek-wolf-spirit-infused-blends/ 🍻 👍
.
.
The New Line:
.
Bourbon Prime: This rich, smoky and spicy bourbon-infused blend redefines traditional prime rib rubs with innovative flavor notes of mushroom, butter, Worcestershire, and even seaweed.
Food: Grilled Tomahawk Steaks w/Butter
Drink: Black Truffle Old Fashioned - Truffle fat washed bourbon with vanilla bean simple syrup and bitters.
.
Lemon Chili Rye: This smoky, slightly bitter and rye-infused blend finishes with an approachable heat and perfectly balanced acidity. With a sweet, fruity and nutty aroma, experiment with the flavors of this complex blend.
Food: Skewered Shrimp w/Lemon Garlic Sauce
Drink: Watermelon Sugar Rye - Watermelon juice with some classic rye whiskey and Lemon Chili Rye infused simple syrup.
.
Smoked Chipotle Mezcal: With a peppery citrus aroma, this spicy and smoky mezcal-infused blend emulates the experience of sipping mezcal with a citrus back.
Food: Grilled Lobster Tails w/Garlic Herb Butter
Drink: The Chill-potle - Ancho Reyes liqueur, smoky mezcal, spicy bitters and Cointreau rimmed with equal parts Smoked Chipotle Mezcal & Chile Con Limon.
.
Sweet Teriyaki Sake: With notes of sweet, spicy and fermentation from the soy, this sake-infused blend brings a delicious sweet heat to practically any protein.
Food: Coal Roasted Shishito Peppers
Drink: Year of the Dragon - Dragonfruit infused gin + sake, club soda, mint and topped with sake.
.
.
.
#overthefirecooking
